.SH "NAME"
PPE_byte \- generate \*(Aqparallel poll enable\*(Aq command byte
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.sp
.ft B
.nf
#include <gpib/ib\&.h>
.fi
.ft
.HP \w'uint8_t\ PPE_byte('u
.BI "uint8_t PPE_byte(unsigned\ int\ " "dio_line" ", int\ " "sense" ");"
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
PPE_byte() returns a \*(Aqparallel poll enable\*(Aq
command byte
corresponding to the
\fIdio_line\fR
and
\fIsense\fR
arguments\&. The
\fIdio_line\fR
(valid values are 1 through 8) specifies which dio line the device being configured should use to send back its parallel poll response\&. The
\fIsense\fR
argument specifies the polarity of the response\&. If
\fIsense\fR
is nonzero, then the specified dio line will be asserted to indicate that the \*(Aqindividual status bit\*(Aq (or \*(Aqist\*(Aq) is 1\&. If
\fIsense\fR
is zero, then the specified dio line will be asserted when ist is zero\&.
.SH "RETURN VALUE"
.PP
The appropriate PPE command byte is returned\&.
